2. cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of algebraic structures of codes, which is a topic of interest in discrete mathematics. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves the construction of codes based on matrix products, which is a topic of interest in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Self-orthogonal codes have applications in cryptography and security, which makes this sub-category a likely fit. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper involves the study of the complexity of constructing Hermitian self-orthogonal codes, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity.
